sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>controller-runtime
    participant Pods as Training Pods<br/>(master/worker)
    participant HeadlessSvc as Headless Service<br/>DNS Discovery
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>(openshift-monitoring)

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 1: Training Job Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: POST PyTorchJob/TFJob/etc CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-*<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS (self-signed TLS)<br/>Auth: API server cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (allow/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created (or rejected)

    Note over Operator,Pods: Flow 1 (continued): Resource Creation

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch for training job CRs<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: CR event (Added/Modified)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Pods (master, worker replicas)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create headless Service<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy (PyTorchJob)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create HPA (elastic PyTorchJob)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token

    Note over Pods,HeadlessSvc: Flow 2: Distributed Training Communication

    Pods->>HeadlessSvc: DNS lookup for peer pods<br/>TCP plaintext
    HeadlessSvc-->>Pods: Pod IP addresses
    Pods->>Pods: Direct pod-to-pod communication<br/>TCP plaintext<br/>NetworkPolicy enforced

    Note over Prometheus,Operator: Flow 3: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Operator: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext<br/>Auth: None (PodMonitor)
    Operator-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics
